The weather in London is famously **changeable and mild**, but here's a typical overview:

1.  **Generally Temperate:**  
    London has a maritime climate, meaning winters are rarely very cold and summers rarely very hot compared to many other locations at similar latitudes.  
    - **Winter (Dec-Feb):** Chilly, damp, often cloudy. Average highs: 5-8°C (41-46°F), lows near freezing. Snow is infrequent and rarely heavy, but can cause disruption. Rain is common.  
    - **Spring (Mar-May):** Gradual warming, increasing sunshine, but still prone to rain showers ("April showers"). Average highs: 11-17°C (52-63°F).  
    - **Summer (Jun-Aug):** Warmest season. Average highs: 18-23°C (64-73°F), but heatwaves can push temperatures above 30°C (86°F) occasionally. Can be sunny or grey/overcast. Humidity builds during warmer spells. Thunderstorms possible.  
    - **Autumn (Sep-Nov):** Cooling temperatures, increasing cloud and rainfall. Can be pleasant and crisp early on, becoming wetter and cooler later. Average highs: 14-19°C (57-66°F) early, dropping to 7-12°C (45-54°F) late.  

2.  **Rain:**  
    Spells of rain occur throughout the year. It's a misconception that it rains *constantly*; rain often comes in frequent but relatively **light showers** rather than prolonged downpours (though those happen too). Winter tends to be the wettest season overall. Always wise to carry an umbrella or a light raincoat.

3.  **Cloud & Sunshine:**  
    Cloud cover is frequent year-round. Summers have the most sunshine hours (up to 8 per day on average), winter the least (around 1-2 per day). Dull, grey days are common, especially between November and February.

4.  **Key Characteristics:**  
    - **"4 Seasons in a Day":** This saying is common! Sunshine, clouds, rain, and wind can all occur within a short time frame. Be prepared for changes.  
    - **Day-to-Day Variation:** Very common. A sunny day can precede or follow a cold, wet one.  
    - **Regional Variation:** Can be drier & warmer in central London than the outskirts; higher ground (like Hampstead/Highgate) can be slightly cooler/wetter.  
    - **Air Quality:** Generally good, but local pollution can build up in dense urban areas on still days.

**For Exact & Current Conditions:**  
Because the weather changes so rapidly, **always check a reliable forecast close to your visit or activity.** Services like these provide real-time and future forecasts:

*   **BBC Weather (London):** [https://www.bbc.co.uk/weather](https://www.bbc.co.uk/weather)
*   **Met Office (London):** [https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/](https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/)
*   **AccuWeather (London):** [https://www.accuweather.com/](https://www.accuweather.com/)

**Packing Tip:** **Layers are key!** Combined with a waterproof jacket and comfortable walking shoes, they prepare you for anything London weather might throw at you.
